profile_positions.description:
Development of a cost-effective laser method to induce superplastic behavior on metallic films for molding with help of reusable silicon nanoscale molds:
- Preparation of different substrates to perform laser shock imprinting;
- Optimization of the laser power and dwelling time in order to induce superplasticity for different substrates;
- Replication of different types of molds on different metal substrates with optimal conditions of laser exposure;
